videos.description: Khadeem Lattin receives a bounce pass from Trae Young but opts for a wide-open Rashard Odomes as the big man knocks down a 3-pointer for the Sooners.
videos.headline: OU ball movement sets up Odomes 3

videos.description: Jordan Shepherd steals the ball back for Oklahoma and finds Trae Young who feeds Jamuni McNeace with a behind-the-back pass for the dunk.
videos.headline: Young goes behind-the-back to McNeace

videos.description: Trae Young's 3-pointer from the mid-court logo is quickly answered by Iowa State with a putback dunk by Cameron Lard.
videos.headline: Young hits from the logo before Iowa State answers

videos.description: Donovan Jackson pulls up in transition to put the Cyclones up 28-14.
videos.headline: Iowa State doubles up OU with 3

videos.description: Trae Young runs the baseline, drawing away three defenders, which opens the paint for a Jamuni McNeace dunk.
videos.headline: Young draws defenders to feed McNeace

videos.description: Trae Young cuts Oklahoma's deficit to 10 at the half after a steal and score.
videos.headline: Young steals and scores before half

videos.description: Iowa State's Solomon Young scores but is quickly matches by a reverse layup from Trae Young for the Sooners.
videos.headline: Iowa State score answered by Trae Young reverse

videos.description: Lindell Wigginton rolls off the screen to knock down a 3-pointer to put Iowa State up 59-50.
videos.headline: Wigginton hits 3 off screen for Cyclones

videos.description: Cameron Lard's putback dunk is quickly followed by a slam in transition by Zoran Talley Jr. for Iowa State.
videos.headline: Cyclones get back-to-back slams

videos.description: Trae Young fires a long ball to Brady Manek, cutting Oklahoma's deficit to 9.
videos.headline: Young lobs to Manek for oop

videos.description: Trae Young wills his way to the hoop for an up-and-under basket through traffic and a foul for the Sooners.
videos.headline: Young spins in for and-1

videos.description: Trae Young drives to the right and draws a foul but cuts his knee as he falls to the floor as the Sooners cut the deficit to 1.
videos.headline: Young scrapes knee after hard foul, bucket

videos.description: Donovan Jackson is left open in the corner for the 3-pointer that puts Iowa State up 80-77.
videos.headline: Jackson hits corner 3 for Cyclones

videos.description: Solomon Young leaps to deflect the ball and gets it to Lindell Wigginton who hits a quick 3-pointer to put the Cyclones up 6.
videos.headline: Wigginton buries 3 for Iowa State

videos.description: Lindell Wigginton joins Doug Sherman and Robbie Hummel after his 26 points helped take down Trae Young and the No. 17 Sooners.
videos.headline: Wigginton key for Cyclones in victory over OU

videos.description: Trae Young scores 22 points and hands out 11 assists in Oklahoma's 88-80 loss to Iowa State.
